Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of wireless communication channels, specifically lognormal fading channels, and proposes a new framework for analyzing the asymptotic outage probabilities of diversity receptions. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of channel correlation on performance, which is related to system dynamics and control (cs.SY) and modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
